flowmux is an unofficial Linux/GTK4 reimplementation inspired by cmux
(https://github.com/manaflow-ai/cmux), a macOS/AppKit terminal for AI
coding agents. cmux is dual-licensed (GPL-3.0-or-later OR commercial);
flowmux is distributed only under GPL-3.0-or-later.

Because cmux is available under GPL-3.0-or-later, the upstream copyright
notice is preserved:

    Copyright (c) 2024-present Manaflow, Inc.

flowmux does not redistribute cmux source code; it independently
reimplements observable behavior described in cmux's public
documentation (README, cmux.com/docs, CHANGELOG, configuration schemas)
for Linux desktop environments. See docs/UPSTREAM.md for the upstream
tracking policy and docs/upstream-mapping/ for the per-feature mapping.

Trademarks
----------

"cmux" and "Manaflow" are not used as project, package, binary, or
distribution names by flowmux. The "flowmux" name is intentionally distinct.
References to cmux in documentation are for attribution and behavioral
reference only.

